result.execSummary:
The defendant Tania J Milton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tania J Milton in court with attorney Daniel James Chapman.  Defendant Tania J Milton in custody.  Thomas H Frost appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls case and appearances. Also has 16 CF 47.  State speaks to the court.  Atty Chapman speaks to the court. State moves to remove the enhancer in 16 CF 47. Court grants motion.  Court questions the def. re: the plea questionaire and waiver of rights form.  Court finds the def. freely and knowingly waives her rights. Court finds there is a factual basis in both cases.

16 CF 43--Def. pleas guilty. Court accepts plea and finds the def. guilty. 

16 CF 47--Def. pleas guilty. Court accepts plea and finds the def. guilty. 
State speaks re: sentencing, recommending 6 years actual confinement in 16 CF 43, and 3 years confinement in 16 CF 47.
Attorney Chapman argues state's recomendation and asks for 3 years in and 3 years on E.S.  State speaks to the court.  Court speaks to the parties.  Ms. Milton makes statement to the court.  

Sentencing:
16 CF 43--4 years Initial Confinement, with 2 year on E.S.
Eligible for programs.  + costs  AODA Assessment, Absolute Sobriety

16 CF 47--3 years 6 months Initial Confinement in WI Prison System
Not eligible for programs.  + costs

Cases concurrent w/  Washburn County Case 14 CF 143

Credit:  154 days.
